section.section:
"Home builder" includes:
a custom home builder as defined in § 10-501 of the Real Property Article;
a new home builder subject to § 10-301 of the Real Property Article;
the installer or retailer of a mobile home or an industrialized building intended for residential use; and
a person that enters into a contract with a consumer under which the person agrees to provide the consumer with a new home.

"Home builder" does not include:
an employee of a registrant who does not hold himself or herself out for hire in home building except as an employee of a registrant;
subcontractors or other vendors hired by the registrant to perform services or supply materials for the construction of a new home who do not otherwise meet the requirements of this title;
the manufacturer of industrialized buildings intended for residential use or of mobile homes, unless the manufacturer also installs the industrialized buildings or mobile homes;
a real estate developer who does not construct, or enter into contracts with consumers to provide or construct, homes;
a financial institution that lends funds for the construction or purchase of residential dwellings in the State;
except as otherwise provided in this title, a person who erects or constructs new homes solely in Montgomery County; or
a buyer's agent, as defined in § 17-530 of the Business Occupations and Professions Article, when representing a prospective buyer in the purchase of a new home.

"New home" includes:
a custom home as defined in § 10-501(c) of the Real Property Article;
a new home to which § 10-301 of the Real Property Article applies;
an industrialized building intended for residential use; and
a mobile home.
